# Horde AMI Build Guide

Generated by `fabrica horde ami build` for Horde **{{ .Version }}** ({{ .Install }} install) in `{{ .Region }}`.

## Overview

`fabrica horde create` requires a pre-baked AMI containing:

| Component   | Version  | systemd unit   |
|-------------|----------|----------------|
| Ubuntu      | 22.04 LTS| —              |
| MongoDB     | 7.0      | `mongod`       |
| Redis       | 6.2+     | `redis-server` |
| Horde server| {{ .Version }}  | `horde`        |

Fabrica's cloud-init only configures and starts services — it does not install software.

## Generated Files

- `image-builder-recipe.json` — AWS EC2 Image Builder recipe (input to `aws imagebuilder create-image-recipe`)
- `component.yaml` — Image Builder Component document (input to `aws imagebuilder create-component`)
{{- if .IncludePacker }}
- `packer.pkr.hcl` — Packer HCL template (use with `packer init` + `packer build`)
{{- end }}
- `build-guide.md` — this file

