## Verifying the AMI

After launching a test instance from your new AMI:

```bash
systemctl is-enabled mongod redis-server horde
mongosh --eval "db.adminCommand('ping')"
ls -la /etc/horde/
```

Then verify Fabrica can build the provisioning plan:

```bash
fabrica horde create --dry-run
```

## Common Pitfalls

| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| `mongod` not healthy at cloud-init time | Add startup readiness checks to the AMI |
| `horde` unit not found | Unit must be named exactly `horde` |
| `/etc/horde/Server.json` not read | Set `Horde__DataDir=/etc/horde` in the service env |
| `redis` unit not found | Fabrica tries `redis-server` then `redis`; ensure one exists |
| AMI in wrong region | Re-copy the AMI to each deployment region |
| Architecture mismatch | Build the AMI on the same instance family (x86_64 for m7i) |
| Image Builder rejects the recipe | The placeholder `REPLACE_WITH_CUSTOM_COMPONENT_ARN` was not substituted |
